  "title": "Technician (Mechanical Equipment/Pharma)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job scope:</strong></p><ul><li>Carry out maintenance activities in compliance with established procedures, good engineering practices, and cGMP requirements.</li><li>Execute preventive and predictive maintenance for plant equipment and facilities to ensure optimal reliability and uptime.</li><li>Assist in the development of preventive maintenance SOPs, procedures, and task lists to preserve plant assets.</li><li>Diagnose and resolve equipment issues by observing mechanical operations, listening for abnormalities, and using appropriate measuring and testing instruments.</li><li>Participate in continuous improvement initiatives and support IRS/QAR investigations.</li><li>Support plant equipment and system projects, including construction and commissioning, through active involvement in punch list closure and commissioning activities; collaborate with supervisors and\nengineers on equipment improvements and modifications.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>O level/Nitec/Diploma in mechanical engineering </li><li>Mechanical technician experience from pharmaceutical, chemical, or petrochemical industries</li><li>Ability to perform Mechanical Equipment Troubleshooting and Analysis Skills</li></ul>",
